The following code is intended to assign a letter grade so that a score of 90 or above earns `"A"`, 80–89 earns `"B"`, 70–79 earns `"C"`, 60–69 earns `"D"`, and below 60 earns `"F"`. When `score` is `95`, the code prints `"D"` instead of `"A"`. What is the cause of the bug?

```java
int score = 95;
String grade;
if (score >= 60)
    grade = "D";
else if (score >= 70)
    grade = "C";
else if (score >= 80)
    grade = "B";
else if (score >= 90)
    grade = "A";
else
    grade = "F";
System.out.println(grade);
```

